CORE PRACTICERAPID PROTOTYPING
Prototype First, Deck Second
My default response to a new idea, feature, or concept isn't a slide — it's a working version
someone can click. A stakeholder or investor engaging with a real interface makes a faster,
better-informed call than one reading a description of it. I've built this into a repeatable
process rather than a one-off trick, and I use different tools depending on the surface I'm
prototyping. 
